-- Retired: the SQL word-case surface chain
--   word_case_class_surface(word) -> word_case_map_surface(word, map)
--     -> grapheme_case_target(grapheme, map)
-- is fully superseded by the native, batched word_case_variants (src/lexical_case.c),
-- which is what word_case_variant_ids -> lexical_peers and every live caller now use.
-- The old chain fanned one lexical lookup into O(3 * graphemes) non-inlinable
-- consensus LIMIT-1 subqueries plus O(graphemes) render_text SPI calls (the RBAR on
-- the hot senses/define/bubble_up path). All three were dead in the call graph after
-- the native migration; dropped rather than left as slow, unreachable code.
DROP FUNCTION IF EXISTS word_case_class_surface(bytea);
DROP FUNCTION IF EXISTS word_case_map_surface(bytea, text);
DROP FUNCTION IF EXISTS grapheme_case_target(bytea, text);
